.TH GETPID 2
.SH NAME
getpid, getppid \- get process and parent process IDs
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
#include <unistd.h>

pid_t getpid(void);
pid_t getppid(void);
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B getpid()
function returns the process ID of the calling process.
The
.B getppid()
function returns the process ID of the parent of the calling process.
.SH RETURN VALUES
The
.B getpid()
and
.B getppid()
functions always return the requested process ID.
.SH SEE ALSO
fork(2)
